name: pulumi-command
summary: the pulumi command provider enables you to execute commands and scripts either locally or remotely as part of the pulumi resource model.
documentation_summary: The HTML text provides information about the "pulumi-command" package version 0.9.2, released on October 31, 2023, available on PyPI (Python Package Index). This package enables the execution of commands and scripts locally or remotely as part of the Pulumi resource model, supporting stateful command execution during resource creation and destruction. It's useful for scenarios like registering resources with external services or running cleanup operations. The package supports various Pulumi languages including C#, Go, JavaScript/TypeScript, and Python, and requires Python version 3.7 or higher. It is licensed under Apache-2.0 and is currently in preview, indicating that the API may change based on user feedback.
